# CSS Code Style — Яндекс.Практикум

## Validation
- Write valid CSS. Use W3C CSS validator to check. Fix all errors.

## Selectors & Naming
- Use class selectors for ALL styling — including typography and layout.
- Never style bare HTML element names: `h1 {}`, `p {}`, `div {}`, `span {}`, `a {}`, `ul {}` are FORBIDDEN.
  Exception: `html {}` and `body {}` are allowed only for global resets (font-size baseline, font-smoothing, box-sizing). Everything else uses classes.
- Never style by ID (`#id-name {}`). Use classes.
- Use BEM methodology for class naming.
- Names must reflect purpose, not appearance. `.gallery {}` is correct. `.button-green {}` or `.abyrvalg {}` are wrong.

## Values
- Do NOT add units after zero values: `margin: 0;` not `margin: 0px;`.
  Exception: when units are critical for cross-browser compatibility.
- ALWAYS write leading zero for decimals between -1 and 1: `font-size: 0.8em;` not `font-size: .8em;`.
- Shorten hex color codes when possible: `#ebc` not `#eebbcc;`.

## Formatting Rules
- One space between property and value, NO space before colon:
```css
  /* Wrong */
  font-weight:bold;
  /* Correct */
  font-weight: bold;
```
- Opening curly brace `{` on the SAME line as the selector, with one space before it:
```css
  /* Wrong */
  .video{
  /* Correct */
  .video {
```
- Each declaration on its own separate line.
- Semicolon after EVERY declaration, including the last one.
- Empty line between separate rules (double newline).

## Indentation
- Indent block content inside rules (nested rules, declarations) with 2 spaces.
```css
  @media screen {
    html {
      background: #fff;
    }
  }
```

## Quotes
- Use single quotes `''` in CSS for attribute values and property values.
- For external URLs — no quotes: `url(https://example.com/font.woff2)`.
- For local relative paths — single quotes required: `url('./vendor/normalize.css')`.
- Exception: `@charset` rule requires double quotes.
```css
  /* Wrong */
  @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans");
  font-family: "open sans", arial;
  /* Correct — external URL, no quotes */
  @import url(https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans);
  font-family: 'open sans', arial;
  /* Correct — local path, single quotes */
  @import url('./vendor/normalize.css');
  @import url('./blocks/header/header.css');
```

## Organization
- Split CSS into thematic sections with comment headers.
- Separate sections with empty lines.
```css
  /* Header */

  .header {}

  /* Gallery */

  .gallery {}

  /* Footer */

  .footer {}
```

## No Hacks
- Do NOT use browser detection or CSS hacks (user-agent sniffing, CSS filters/tricks for specific browsers).
- Solve cross-browser issues with standard methods. Hacks make code unpredictable and unmaintainable.

## Working with Existing Code
- When editing existing code, preserve the original formatting style of the file.
- Your additions must not stand out visually from the surrounding code.

## Trailing Whitespace
- No trailing spaces at end of lines.
- File must end with a single newline.